dcterms:description: A freely accessible critical care database containing a large collection of EHR data for patients admitted to critical care units, including demographics, lab results, vital measurements, and patient outcomes.
dcterms:title: Medical Information Mart for Intensive Care III (MIMIC-III)

dcterms:creator: A. E. W. Johnson
dcterms:description: A freely accessible electronic health record dataset that improves upon MIMIC-III, incorporating more up-to-date medical data with an optimized data storage structure.
dcterms:title: Medical Information Mart for Intensive Care IV (MIMIC-IV)

dcterms:creator: T. J. Pollard
dcterms:description: A freely available multi-center database for critical care research, containing various information for patients including vital sign measurements and treatment information.
dcterms:title: eICU Collaborative Research Database (eICU)

dcterms:description: The dataset contains daily Google stock data recorded between 2004 and 2019, including features such as volume, high, low, opening, closing, and adjusted closing prices.
dcterms:title: Stocks

dcterms:description: The dataset contains multivariate continuous-valued time series from the UCI Appliances energy prediction data, featuring high-dimensional, correlated, and periodic features.
dcterms:title: Energy
